owever, by hailing him as the one uncreated God (Y. 30.3, 45.2), wholly wise, benevolent and good, Creator as well as upholder of aša (Y. 31.8)."},"website":{"wt":"Iranicaonline.org"},"accessdate":{"wt":"2017-06-14"}},"i":0}}]}' id="mwA5I"><a rel="mw:ExtLink" class="external text" href="http://www.iranicaonline.org/articles/ahura-mazda" id="mwA5M">"Zoroaster gave a wholly new dimension to his worship, however, by hailing him as the one uncreated God (Y. 30.3, 45.2), wholly wise, benevolent and good, Creator as well as upholder of aša (Y. 31.8)"</a>. <i id="mwA5Q">Iranicaonline.org</i><span class="reference-accessdate" id="mwA5U">. Retrieved <span class="nowrap" id="mwA5Y">2017-06-14</span></span>.</cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rft.genre=unknown&amp;rft.jtitle=Iranicaonline.org&amp;rft.atitle=Zoroaster+gave+a+wholly+new+dimension+to+his+worship%2C+however%2C+by+hailing+him+as+the+one+uncreated+God+%28Y.+30.3%2C+45.2%29%2C+wholly+wise%2C+benevolent+and+good%2C+Creator+as+well+as+upholder+of+a%C5%A1a+%28Y.+31.8%29.&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.iranicaonline.org%2Farticles%2Fahura-mazda&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AZoroastrianism" class="Z3988" about="#mwt53" id="mwA5c"></span><link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r879151008" about="#mwt53" typeof="mw:Extension/templatestyles" data-mw='{"name":"templatestyles","attrs":{"src":"Module:Citation/CS1/styles.css"},"body":{"extsrc":""}}' id="mwA5g"/></span></li><li about="#cite_note-21" id="cite_note-21"><a href="./Zoroastrianism#cite_ref-21" rel="mw:referencedBy"><span class="mw-linkback-text">↑ </span></a> <span id="mw-reference-text-cite_note-21" class="mw-reference-text"><cite class="citation web" about="#mwt54" typeof="mw:Transclusion" data-mw='{"parts":[{"template":{"target":{"wt":"cite web","href":"./Template:Cite_web"},"params":{"url":{"wt":"http://www.iranicaonline.org/articles/amesa-spenta-beneficent-"},"title":{"wt":"AMƎŠA SPƎNTA, an Avestan term for beneficent divinity, meaning literally \"Holy/Bounteous Immortal\"... Among Zoroastrian priests today the term is frequently applied to the \"calendrical\" divinities, that is, to all those who have received dedications of the days of the month, together with extra three, Burz Yazad, Hōm, and Dahmān Āfrīn... The term is, however, more often used in a restricted sense for the greatest of the spənta beings, that is, for the great Heptad who belong especially to Zoroaster&apos;s own revelation, namely Ahura Mazdā himself (sometimes together with, or represented by, his Holy Spirit, Spənta Mainyu) and the six whom he first evoked among the yazatas"},"website":{"wt":"Iranicaonline.org"},"accessdate":{"wt":"2017-06-14"}},"i":0}}]}' id="mwA5k"><a rel="mw:ExtLink" class="external text" href="http://www.iranicaonline.org/articles/amesa-spenta-beneficent-" id="mwA5o">"AMƎŠA SPƎNTA, an Avestan term for beneficent divinity, meaning literally "Holy/Bounteous Immortal"... Among Zoroastrian priests today the term is frequently applied to the "calendrical" divinities, that is, to all those who have received dedications of the days of the month, together with extra three, Burz Yazad, Hōm, and Dahmān Āfrīn... The term is, however, more often used in a restricted sense for the greatest of the spənta beings, that is, for the great Heptad who belong especially to Zoroaster's own revelation, namely Ahura Mazdā himself (sometimes together with, or represented by, his Holy Spirit, Spənta Mainyu) and the six whom he first evoked among the yazatas"</a>. <i id="mwA5s">Iranicaonline.org</i><span class="reference-accessdate" id="mwA5w">. Retrieved <span class="nowrap" id="mwA50">2017-06-14</span></span>.</cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rft.genre=unknown&amp;rft.jtitle=Iranicaonline.org&amp;rft.atitle=AM%C6%8E%C5%A0A+SP%C6%8ENTA%2C+an+Avestan+term+for+beneficent+divinity%2C+meaning+literally+%22Holy%2FBounteous+Immortal%22...+Among+Zoroastrian+priests+today+the+term+is+frequently+applied+to+the+%22calendrical%22+divinities%2C+that+is%2C+to+all+those+who+have+received+dedications+of+the+days+of+the+month%2C+together+with+extra+three%2C+Burz+Yazad%2C+H%C5%8Dm%2C+and+Dahm%C4%81n+%C4%80fr%C4%ABn...+The+term+is%2C+however%2C+more+often+used+in+a+restricted+sense+for+the+greatest+of+the+sp%C9%99nta+beings%2C+that+is%2C+for+the+great+Heptad+who+belong+especially+to+Zoroaster%27s+own+revelation%2C+namely+Ahura+Mazd%C4%81+himself+%28sometimes+together+with%2C+or+represented+by%2C+his+Holy+Spirit%2C+Sp%C9%99nta+Mainyu%29+and+the+six+whom+he+first+evoked+among+the+yazatas&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.iranicaonline.org%2Farticles%2Famesa-spenta-beneficent-&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AZoroastrianism" class="Z3988" about="#mwt54" id="mwA54"></span><link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r879151008" about="#mwt54" typeof="mw:Extension/templatestyles" data-mw='{"name":"templatestyles","attrs":{"src":"Module:Citation/CS1/styles.css"},"body":{"extsrc":""}}' id="mwA58"/><link rel="mw:PageProp/Category" href="./Category:All_articles_with_dead_external_links" about="#mwt55" typeof="mw:Transclusion" data-mw='{"parts":[{"template":{"target":{"wt":"dead link","href":"./Template:Dead_link"},"params":{"date":{"wt":"April 2018"},"bot":{"wt":"InternetArchiveBot"},"fix-attempted":{"wt":"yes"}},"i":0}}]}' id="mwA6A"/><link rel="mw:PageProp/Category" href="./Category:Articles_with_dead_external_links_from_April_2018" about="#mwt55" id="mwA6E"/><sup class="noprint Inline-Template" about="#mwt55" id="mwA6I"><span style="white-space: nowrap;" id="mwA6M"><span typeof="mw:Entity" id="mwA6Q">[</span><i id="mwA6U"><a rel="mw:WikiLink" href="./Wikipedia:Link_rot" title="Wikipedia:Link rot" id="mwA6Y"><span title=" Dead link since April 2018" id="mwA6c">permanent dead link</span></a></i><span typeof="mw:Entity" id="mwA6g">]</span></span></sup><link rel="mw:PageProp/Category" href="./Category:Articles_with_permanently_dead_external_links" about="#mwt55" id="mwA6k"/></span></li><li about="#cite_note-22" id="cite_note-22"><a href="./Zoroastrianism#cite_ref-22" rel="mw:referencedBy"><span class="mw-linkback-text">↑ </span></a> <span id="mw-reference-text-cite_note-22" class="mw-reference-text"><cite class="citation web" about="#mwt56" typeof="mw:Transclusion" data-mw='{"parts":[{"template":{"target":{"wt":"cite web","href":"./Template:Cite_web"},"params":{"url":{"wt":"http://www.iranicaonline.org/articles/asa-means-truth-in-avestan"},"title":{"wt":"Since the Aməṧa Spəṇtas represent the totality of good moral qualities, it is easy to understand why, by analogy with the inherited opposition between *ṛtá- &apos;truth&apos; and *drugh- &apos;lie,&apos; the other Aməṧa Spəṇtas were similarly assigned their evil counterparts."},"website":{"wt":"Iranicaonline.org"},"accessdate":{"wt":"2017-06-14"}},"i":0}}]}' id="mwA6o"><a rel="mw:ExtLink" class="external text" href="http://www.iranicaonline.org/articles/asa-means-truth-in-avestan" id="mwA6s">"Since the Aməṧa Spəṇtas represent the totality of good moral qualities, it is easy to understand why, by analogy with the inherited opposition between *ṛtá- 'truth' and *drugh- 'lie,' the other Aməṧa Spəṇtas were similarly assigned their evil counterparts"</a>. <i id="mwA6w">Iranicaonline.org</i><span class="reference-accessdate" id="mwA60">. Retrieved <span class="nowrap" id="mwA64">2017-06-14</span></span>.</cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rft.genre=unknown&amp;rft.jtitle=Iranicaonline.org&amp;rft.atitle=Since+the+Am%C9%99%E1%B9%A7a+Sp%C9%99%E1%B9%87tas+represent+the+totality+of+good+moral+qualities%2C+it+is+easy+to+understand+why%2C+by+analogy+with+the+inherited+opposition+between+%2A%E1%B9%9Bt%C3%A1-+%27truth%27+and+%2Adrugh-+%27lie%2C%27+the+other+Am%C9%99%E1%B9%A7a+Sp%C9%99%E1%B9%87tas+were+similarly+assigned+their+evil+counterparts.&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.iranicaonline.org%2Farticles%2Fasa-means-truth-in-avestan&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AZoroastrianism" class="Z3988" about="#mwt56" id="mwA68"></span><link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r879151008" about="#mwt56" typeof="mw:Extension/templatestyles" data-mw='{"name":"templatestyles","attrs":{"src":"Module:Citation/CS1/styles.css"},"body":{"extsrc":""}}' id="mwA7A"/></span></li><li about="#cite_note-23" id="cite_note-23"><a href="./Zoroastrianism#cite_ref-23" rel="mw:referencedBy"><span class="mw-linkback-text">↑ </span></a> <span id="mw-reference-text-cite_note-23" class="mw-reference-text"><cite class="citation web" about="#mwt57" typeof="mw:Transclusion" data-mw='{"parts":[{"template":{"target":{"wt":"cite web","href":"./Template:Cite_web"},"params":{"url":{"wt":"http://www.avesta.org/dhalla/dhalla1.htm#chap6"},"title":{"wt":"The better one of the two spirits told the evil one that they were by nature opposed to each other in their thoughts and teachings, understandings and beliefs, words, and deeds, selves and souls—in nothing could they twain ever meet."},"website":{"wt":"Avesta.org"},"accessdate":{"wt":"2017-06-14"}},"i":0}}]}' id="mwA7E"><a rel="mw:ExtLink" class="external text" href="http://www.avesta.org/dhalla/dhalla1.htm#chap6" id="mwA7I">"The better one of the two spirits told the evil one that they were by nature opposed to each other in their thoughts and teachings, understandings and beliefs, words, and deeds, selves and souls—in nothing could they twain ever meet"</a>. <i id="mwA7M">Avesta.org</i><span class="reference-accessdate" id="mwA7Q">. Retrieved <span class="nowrap" id="mwA7U">2017-06-14</span></span>.</cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rft.genre=unknown&amp;rft.jtitle=Avesta.org&amp;rft.atitle=The+better+one+of+the+two+spirits+told+the+evil+one+that+they+were+by+nature+opposed+to+each+other+in+their+thoughts+and+teachings%2C+understandings+and+beliefs%2C+words%2C+and+deeds%2C+selves+and+souls%E2%80%94in+nothing+could+they+twain+ever+meet.&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.avesta.org%2Fdhalla%2Fdhalla1.htm%23chap6&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AZoroastrianism" class="Z3988" about="#mwt57" id="mwA7Y"></span><link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r879151008" about="#mwt57" typeof="mw:Extension/templatestyles" data-mw='{"name":"templatestyles","attrs":{"src":"Module:Citation/CS1/styles.css"},"body":{"extsrc":""}}' id="mwA7c"/></span></li><li about="#cite_note-24" id="cite_note-24"><a href="./Zoroastrianism#cite_ref-24" rel="mw:referencedBy"><span class="mw-linkback-text">↑ </span></a> <span id="mw-reference-text-cite_note-24" class="mw-reference-text"><cite class="citation web" about="#mwt58" typeof="mw:Transclusion" data-mw='{"parts":[{"template":{"target":{"wt":"cite web","href":"./Template:Cite_web"},"params":{"url":{"wt":"http://www.iranicaonline.org/articles/ahriman"},"title":{"wt":"In the Gathas Angra Mainyu is the direct opposite of Spənta Mainyu"},"website":{"wt":"Iranicaonline.org"},"accessdate":{"wt":"2017-06-14"}},"i":0}}]}' id="mwA7g"><a rel="mw:ExtLink" class="external text" href="http://www.iranicaonline.org/articles/ahriman" id="mwA7k">"In the Gathas Angra Mainyu is the direct opposite of Spənta Mainyu"</a>. <i id="mwA7o">Iranicaonline.org</i><span class="reference-accessdate" id="mwA7s">. Retrieved <span class="nowrap" id="mwA7w">2017-06-14</span></span>.</cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rft.genre=unknown&amp;rft.jtitle=Iranicaonline.org&amp;rft.atitle=In+the+Gathas+Angra+Mainyu+is+the+direct+opposite+of+Sp%C9%99nta+Mainyu&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.iranicaonline.org%2Farticles%2Fahriman&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AZoroastrianism" class="Z3988" about="#mwt58" id="mwA70"></span><link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r879151008" about="#mwt58" typeof="mw:Extension/templatestyles" data-mw='{"name":"templatestyles","attrs":{"src":"Module:Citation/CS1/styles.css"},"body":{"extsrc":""}}' id="mwA74"/></span></li><li about="#cite_note-25" id="cite_note-25"><a href="./Zoroastrianism#cite_ref-25" rel="mw:referencedBy"><span class="mw-linkback-text">↑ </span></a> <span id="mw-reference-text-cite_note-25" class="mw-reference-text"><cite class="citation web" about="#mwt59" typeof="mw:Transclusion" data-mw='{"parts":[{"template":{"target":{"wt":"cite web","href":"./Template:Cite_web"},"params":{"url":{"wt":"http://www.iranicaonline.org/articles/ahriman"},"title":{"wt":"\"The daēvas are said (Y. 32.3) to be the offspring, not of Angra Mainyu, but of Akəm Manah (&apos;evil thinking&apos;). But in Y. 30.6 it is the &apos;deceiver,&apos; dəbaaman, most probably Angra Mainyu, who induces them to choose acištəm manah (&apos;The worst thinking&apos;).\" The name Angra Mainyu appears only once (Y. 45.2), when the \"more bounteous of the spirits twain\" declares his absolute antithesis to the \"evil\" one in all things. \"At the beginning of creation, the recital of the Ahuna Vairya prayer by Ahura Mazdā put Angra Mainyu to flight (Y. 19. 15). Angra Mainyu created Aži Dahāka (Y. 9.8); but he recoiled in fear from Mithra&apos;s mace (Yt. 10.97 and 134). He broke into Aša&apos;s creation (Yt. 13.77) but had to flee from the face of the earth (Yt. 17.19) when Zoroaster was born.\""},"website":{"wt":"Iranicaonline.org"},"accessdate":{"wt":"2017-06-14"}},"i":0}}]}' id="mwA78"><a rel="mw:ExtLink" class="external text" href="http://www.iranicaonline.org/articles/ahriman" id="mwA8A">"<span class="cs1-kern-left" id="mwA8E">"</span>The daēvas are said (Y. 32.3) to be the offspring, not of Angra Mainyu, but of Akəm Manah ('evil thinking'). But in Y. 30.6 it is the 'deceiver,' dəbaaman, most probably Angra Mainyu, who induces them to choose acištəm manah ('The worst thinking')." The name Angra Mainyu appears only once (Y. 45.2), when the "more bounteous of the spirits twain" declares his absolute antithesis to the "evil" one in all things. "At the beginning of creation, the recital of the Ahuna Vairya prayer by Ahura Mazdā put Angra Mainyu to flight (Y. 19. 15). Angra Mainyu created Aži Dahāka (Y. 9.8); but he recoiled in fear from Mithra's mace (Yt. 10.97 and 134). He broke into Aša's creation (Yt. 13.77) but had to flee from the face of the earth (Yt. 17.19) when Zoroaster was born.<span class="cs1-kern-right" id="mwA8I">"</span>"</a>. <i id="mwA8M">Iranicaonline.org</i><span class="reference-accessdate" id="mwA8Q">. Retrieved <span class="nowrap" id="mwA8U">2017-06-14</span></span>.</cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rft.genre=unknown&amp;rft.jtitle=Iranicaonline.org&amp;rft.atitle=%22The+da%C4%93vas+are+said+%28Y.+32.3%29+to+be+the+offspring%2C+not+of+Angra+Mainyu%2C+but+of+Ak%C9%99m+Manah+%28%27evil+thinking%27%29.+But+in+Y.+30.6+it+is+the+%27deceiver%2C%27+d%C9%99baaman%2C+most+probably+Angra+Mainyu%2C+who+induces+them+to+choose+aci%C5%A1t%C9%99m+manah+%28%27The+worst+thinking%27%29.%22+The+name+Angra+Mainyu+appears+only+once+%28Y.+45.2%29%2C+when+the+%22more+bounteous+of+the+spirits+twain%22+declares+his+absolute+antithesis+to+the+%22evil%22+one+in+all+things.+%22At+the+beginning+of+creation%2C+the+recital+of+the+Ahuna+Vairya+prayer+by+Ahura+Mazd%C4%81+put+Angra+Mainyu+to+flight+%28Y.+19.+15%29.+Angra+Mainyu+created+A%C5%BEi+Dah%C4%81ka+%28Y.+9.8%29%3B+but+he+recoiled+in+fear+from+Mithra%27s+mace+%28Yt.+10.97+and+134%29.+He+broke+into+A%C5%A1a%27s+creation+%28Yt.+13.77%29+but+had+to+flee+from+the+face+of+the+earth+%28Yt.+17.19%29+when+Zoroaster+was+born.%22&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.iranicaonline.org%2Farticles%2Fahriman&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AZoroastrianism" class="Z3988" about="#mwt59" id="mwA8Y"></span><link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style